      • containsMethod

        public boolean containsMethod(java.lang.String methodName)
        Get whether or not the ClassDeclaration contains the Method with the specified name.

        For example: 
         public class ClassName
 {
        public void doSomething()
        {
                ...
        }
 }

        A call like: "containsMethod("doSomething")" would return true.
        Parameters:
        methodName - The name of the method to search for.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the ClassDeclaration contains the Method with the specified name.

      • getMethods

        public MethodDeclaration[] getMethods(java.lang.String methodName)
        Get the ClassDeclaration's Method with the specified name.

        For example: 
         public class ClassName
 {
        public void doSomething()
        {
                ...
        }
 }

        A call like: "getMethod("doSomething")" would return the Method for the "doSomething" method.
        Parameters:
        methodName - The name of the method to search for.
        Returns:
        The Method for the method, if it exists.
